# Code Quality Standards

- Write clean, readable, idiomatic code for the chosen language
- Prefer explicit over implicit; avoid "magic" that obscures behavior
- Handle errors properly -- never swallow exceptions or silently fail
- Use meaningful, descriptive names; avoid abbreviations unless they are domain-standard (e.g. `id`, `url`, `http`)
- Keep functions small and single-purpose; if a function does two things, split it
- No dead code, no commented-out code -- use version control instead
- Include type annotations / type hints where the language supports them
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Keep dependencies minimal; justify each one
- Reference the ADRs in .docs/adr/ for architectural context before making structural changes
